How Late Do U Have 2 B B4 U R Absent?
Up in It
The most surprising thing about George Clinton's first album of new
material in almost a decade isn't how long it took to arrive; it's
that it's not terribly funky. Recorded over several years, How Late
sounds alternately like an audio diary and a slow party, long on
spoken-word pieces and bland pop...
Perry Farrell loves the Eighties, George Clinton sends Sly fighting words
February 3, 2006